MISS South Africa 2021 Lalela Mswane has proved once again why she has a heart of gold. She visited Inanda Newtown Comprehensive School on Monday, 7 February, where she handed over the newly-renovated consumer studies classroom in collaboration with the Sibaya Casino and Entertainment Kingdom. Speaking during the handover, Lalela, who placed second at the Miss Universe pageant, said the visit was inspiring. “It was also incredibly inspiring to see the impact an investment such as this can make in the lives of young people in pursuit of their dreams,” she said. ALSO READ | LERATO MVELASE GOES BACK TO SCHOOL “I would encourage more initiatives such as Sun International’s Adopt the School Project because an investment in education is ultimately an investment in the future of our country.” Speaking on behalf of the Sibaya Casino and Entertainment Kingdom, which donated R300 000, general manager Myan Moodley said he and the Sibaya team remained committed to continuing to improve facilities at the school. Inanda Newtown principal, Thulile Khumalo, said they were grateful for the donation. “These improvements are not only going to benefit our pupils, but also the community as these pupils will be applying the skills gained at school at home.”